description.short: Divides two integers and pushes the result back onto the stack.
description.long:
Pops two integers from the stack, divides the second one by the first one and pushes the result back onto the stack.
Formula: `q = floor(x / y)`.

exit_codes.condition: Top or second element is not an Int.

description.short: Divides two integers, rounds the result and pushes it back onto the stack.
description.long:
Pops two integers from the stack, divides the second one by the first one, rounds the result and pushes it back onto the stack.
Formula: `q = round(x / y)`.

exit_codes.condition: Top or second element is not an Int.

description.short: Divides two integers, rounds the result up and pushes it back onto the stack.
description.long:
Pops two integers from the stack, divides the second one by the first one, rounds the result up and pushes it back onto the stack.
Formula: `q = ceil(x / y)`.

exit_codes.condition: Top or second element is not an Int.

description.long: Divides two integers and pushes the remainder back onto the stack.
Divides two integers (in reverse order) and pushes the remainder back onto the stack.
Divides two integers and pushes the quotient and remainder back onto the stack.
Divides two integers (in reverse order) and pushes the quotient and remainder back onto the stack.
Calculates `q = round(x * y / z)` and `r = x * y - z * q`.
Calculates `q = ceil(x * y / z)` and `r = x * y - z * q`.
